# Series 2

## Exercise 2.1

### A






::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
# create timeseries object
t <- seq(1, 100, length = 100)
data <- 0.5 * t + 1 + runif(100, -1, 1)

ts <- ts(data)
plot(ts)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-1.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
length(ts)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] 100
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code}
# Applying backward differencing
ts.2 <- diff(ts, lag = 1)
plot(ts.2)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-2.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
length(ts.2)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] 99
```


:::
:::






The new time series are 99 units long instead of 100.

